			<description><![CDATA[<h2 id="whoarewe">
Who are we?</h2>
<p>
We are about making it easier for companies to get paid. By building mindful automation and powerful tools wrapped in easy to use interfaces, we&rsquo;re making companies more informed and sophisticated, reducing the time it takes to get their incoming money.</p>
<p>
Our <a href="http://www.zencash.com/about">about page</a> shows the team so far.</p>
<p>
We use Macs, Github, Pivotal Tracker, Basecamp, Campfire, Sublime Text, practice BDD, pair programming and our own version of SCRUM. We iterate quickly and release frequently.</p>
<h2 id="whatweneed">
What we need</h2>
<p>
Any combination of the following: full stack Ruby on Rails engineer, front end engineer, back end engineer.</p>
<p>
Our stack is MRI, Ruby on Rails, Backbone.js, CoffeeScript, RSpec, MySQL, Redis, Resque, Eventmachine.</p>
<h3 id="generaltraits">
General traits</h3>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>
Good written and spoken English</li>
<li>
BDD/TDD experience</li>
<li>
Mac, Linux environments</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="fullstackrailsdeveloper">
Full stack Rails developer</h3>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
What we are looking for:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Ability to go up and down the stack as needed: you can slice PSDs into HTML/CSS, write client-side JS, code back end models, views and controllers, hand optimize a SQL query and install a custom version of libxml2 from source.</li>
<li>
Tests first, BDD/TDD.</li>
<li>
Experience with the latest front-end technologies, such as Haml, SCSS, and JavaScript and / or CoffeeScript, rich frameworks such as Ember.js, Backbone.js.</li>
<li>
Experience with Ruby on Rails.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Bonus points:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience with infrastructure automation: Chef, Puppet etc.</li>
<li>
Application deployment to the cloud (Amazon, Rackspace, Engine Yard, Heroku, etc.)</li>
<li>
Experience with RSpec, Cucumber, Capybara</li>
<li>
Experience with upgrading from Rails 2.3 to 3</li>
<li>
Unix scripting skills</li>
</ul>
<p>
Yes, basically a one-man army. Not looking for a ninja, in case you were wondering. All ninja positions are currently filled.</p>
<h3 id="frontenddeveloper">
Front end developer</h3>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
What we are looking for:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Excellent knowledge of JavaScript, HTML and CSS.</li>
<li>
Experience with client side frameworks such as Backbone.js, Ember.js.</li>
<li>
Basic understanding of server side frameworks such as Ruby on Rails or Django.</li>
<li>
Photoshop experience.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Bonus points:</p>
<ul>
<li>
CoffeeScript</li>
<li>
Experience in real-time communication via Websockets, Socket.io or similar technology</li>
<li>
Experience with RSpec, Cucumber, Capybara, Jasmine</li>
<li>
Experience with Amazon Web Services</li>
<li>
Experience with WordPress theme development</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="backendrailsdeveloper">
Back end Rails developer</h3>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
What we are looking for:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Ruby, Ruby on Rails knowledge</li>
<li>
Understanding of scaling techniques such as caching, database query optimization, and asynchronous / background job queues</li>
<li>
Knowledge of NoSQL data stores.</li>
<li>
Experience working with 3rd party APIs: REST, SOAP (yes, we are consuming some SOAP, sorry)</li>
</ul>
<p>
Bonus points:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience with event-driven systems such as EventMachine, Node.js, Twisted.</li>
<li>
Experience with RSpec, Cucumber, Capybara</li>
<li>
Experience with infrastructure automation: Chef, Puppet etc.</li>
<li>
Application deployment to the cloud (Amazon, Rackspace, Engine Yard, Heroku, etc.)</li>
<li>
Scaling web applications</li>
<li>
Service-Oriented Architecture</li>
<li>
Experience with upgrading from Rails 2.3 to 3</li>
<li>
Unix scripting skills</li>
</ul>
